To hide or show code, we can use

M-x hs-minor-mode

Here are some useful command from GNU Emacs Manual:

Hide current block: M-x hs-hide-block
Show current block: M-x hs-show-block
Either hide or show current block: M-x hs-toggle-hiding

Hide all top level blocks: M-x hs-hide-all
show all top level blocks: M-x hs-show-all

Automatically open hs-minor-mode when in c/c++ mode:

(add-hook 'c-mode-common-hook 'hs-minor-mode)
